        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer192815580" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14241811052890693997">As far as airport novels go, this book was a sleeper...the kind that literally puts you to sleep. That&apos;s an odd thing to say about a book that has some of the loudest prose I&apos;ve ever read, the kind that shouts, shoots, and explodes on every page. But I found it rather dull. I liked the premise and there was a nice amount of science-babble in it. Yet Rollin&apos;s cardboard characters with their TV formula problems bored me. This is the first Rollins novel I&apos;ve read. I know a number of people who like</span>
  <span id="freeText14241811052890693997" style="display:none">As far as airport novels go, this book was a sleeper...the kind that literally puts you to sleep. That's an odd thing to say about a book that has some of the loudest prose I've ever read, the kind that shouts, shoots, and explodes on every page. But I found it rather dull. I liked the premise and there was a nice amount of science-babble in it. Yet Rollin's cardboard characters with their TV formula problems bored me. This is the first Rollins novel I've read. I know a number of people who like his brand of techno-thriller but he comes across to me as a poor man's Micheal Crichton. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14241811052890693997" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

