<span id="freeTextContainer9471330189646679917">I wasn&apos;t too impressed with this one. The first half was setting the stage for what was to come and was mostly the characters attempting to eliminate a throwback creature. The remainder of the novel involves genetic manipulation for military purposes. There were some novel science/medical ideas involved besides actual gene manipulation. I was unaware that humans have magnetite crystals in their brains. The stated use and purpose of them in the novel was interesting. </span>
